latestPosts.caption:
All the feels this morning…. Kicking off 2025 wedding szn with two weddings this weekend.

This was my morning with Harsimran ❤️

I’m going into this wedding season with much more ease. Not a lot of brides, a very relaxed schedule, I wanted to really not take what I love doing for granted. We get so caught up in the hustle and bustle of life and an insane schedule that sometimes you forget what you truly do this for. It’s the ART. It’s the love for makeup and making people feel their absolute best. It’s being creative and passionate about the magic you created. 

The schedule can really get to you as a bridal artist, the early mornings and the non stop booking to booking lifestyle. This year I think I can count on both hands how many brides I have. I’m pumped to really put my all into those brides who chose me. It’s a blessing to be able to do what we do as bridal artists, and I am really grateful for all of my past clients for giving me all the experience to get to this point in my career. 

To every single beauty that I’ve glammed in my career, I am really indebted to you ❤️ words can’t express how grateful I am. Thank you. 

Here’s to an exciting 2025 wedding season… can’t wait to show you what looks we have in store for this year

With all the ❤️
-V

latestPosts.caption:
It’s your wedding week but you still want to have fun playful looks… 

The best time to have fun with your look would be on your Jaggo maiya day or mehndi day. Keep your soft and romantic looks for ceremony and reception because you want to be able to look back and do something elegant and timeless. Try the trends and bolder looks on the pre events because that would be the time to do it.  Remember your ceremony look is the most photographed and the reception would be second.
Keep it classic and modern and fresh! 

Go play around with all your prewedding looks and have fun with it! 

Did you have fun with your Jaggo look? Let me know in the comments !
